## 3. Backend Implementation Details

### A. Updating Token Verification Guard
In `login.service.ts` under `validateUser`:

```typescript
async validateUser(payload: any) {
  // If the token belongs to a customer login session
  if (payload.role === Role.CUSTOMER) {
    const customer = await this.CustomerModel.findById(payload._id);
    if (!customer || customer.status === 0 || customer.customer_login_portal === 0) {
      throw new HttpException('Mobile access blocked or customer inactive', HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);
    }

    // Check if logged in as staff
    if (payload.staff_id) {
      const staff = await this.customerStaffModel.findById(payload.staff_id);
      if (!staff || staff.status === 0) {
        throw new HttpException('Staff access deactivated', HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);
      }
      
      // Compare device ID for staff session validation
      if (payload.device_id && staff.device_id && staff.device_id !== payload.device_id) {
        throw new HttpException('Staff logged in on another device', HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED);
      }
      if (staff.token && staff.token !== payload.rawToken) {
        throw new HttpException('Session expired', HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED);
      }
      return customer; // Return parent customer context for API endpoints
    }

    // Standard Customer Owner device id checks
    if (payload.device_id && customer.device_id && customer.device_id !== payload.device_id) {
      throw new HttpException('Owner logged in on another device', HttpStatus.UNAUTHORIZED);
    }
    return customer;
  }
  
  // Regular user validation...
}
```

### B. Admin CRUD Controllers
Allows Admins to manage staff list for any customer:
*   `POST /customer-staff/admin-create` (Create staff for any customer ID)
*   `GET /customer-staff/admin-list/:customerId` (List staff for a customer)

